cancelStream(uint256,bytes,bytes,uint256.details: Throws if the id does not point to a valid stream. Throws if the caller is not the sender or the recipient of the stream. Throws if there is a token transfer failure.

params._proof1: The Dividend proof where the first output note goes to the stream recipient
params._proof2: The Join-Split proof where the first output note goes to the stream recipient
params._unclaimedTime: The amount of time corresponding to the value being sent to the recipient
params.streamId: The id of the stream to cancel.

createStream(address,bytes32,address,uin.details: Throws if paused. Throws if the recipient is the zero address, the contract itself or the caller. Throws if the start time is before `block.timestamp`. Throws if the stop time is before the start time. Throws if the duration calculation has a math error. Throws if the next stream id calculation has a math error. Throws if the contract is not allowed to transfer enough tokens. Throws if there is a token transfer failure.

params.notehash: The note of a zkAsset to be streamed.
params.recipient: The address towards which the money is streamed.
params.startTime: The unix timestamp for when the stream starts.
params.stopTime: The unix timestamp for when the stream stops.
params.tokenAddress: The zkAsset to use as streaming currency.
